				\begin{document}$$F = \Delta {{C}_{i}}\frac{H}{\tau };\,\,\,Q = FS,$$\end{document}where S is the city area, H is the mixing layer height, and ΔCi is the average impurity concentration at the city territory minus the regional background value (urban addition).
